# Paths that change what the build does, or what a Claude session does — both
# deserve review even when the diff looks like prose.
#
# Set OWNER below to a GitHub username (@you) or team (@org/team). Until it's a
# real handle this file does nothing.
#
# CODEOWNERS by itself only *requests* a reviewer. To make it a gate, enable
# branch protection on main: "Require a pull request before merging" plus
# "Require review from Code Owners". See
# .claude/skills/project-conventions/SKILL.md.

# Instructions the model follows. These read like documentation and change
# behaviour like configuration — the combination is why they're listed first.
/.claude/            @OWNER
/CLAUDE.md           @OWNER

# CI: what runs, with what permissions, pinned to which action SHAs.
/.github/            @OWNER

# Supply-chain posture. Changes here should cite the ADR that decided them.
/.npmrc              @OWNER
/pnpm-workspace.yaml @OWNER
/renovate.json       @OWNER
/deny.toml           @OWNER
/Cargo.lock          @OWNER
/pnpm-lock.yaml      @OWNER

# Decisions and their conventions.
/docs/adr/           @OWNER
